Construct a PHP program to extract the mail addresses in the given
string using regular expression.

SOLUTION:
PHP script that extracts all email addresses from a given string using a regular expression.

CODE:
<?php
// Sample string with multiple email addresses
$text = "Contact us at support@example.com, sales@example.org or admin@test.co.in.";

// Regular expression for emails
$pattern = "/[a-zA-Z0-9._%+-]+@[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,}/";

// Extract all email addresses
preg_match_all($pattern, $text, $matches);

// Display results
echo "<h3>Extracted Email Addresses:</h3>";
foreach ($matches[0] as $email) {
    echo $email . "<br>";
}
?>

OUTPUT:
Extracted Email Addresses: support@example.com
sales@example.org<br>admin@test.co.in
